### ============================================
### 🪑 TABLE MANAGEMENT API TESTS
### ============================================
### Prerequisites: 
### 1. Server running on http://localhost:5000
### 2. Admin user created in database
### 3. Run auth tests first to get tokens
### ============================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@adminToken = 
@tableId = 

### ============================================
### 1. GET ALL TABLES - Public (No Auth Required)
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/tables
Content-Type: application/json

### Expected Response: 200 OK
### Returns: Array of all tables with tableNumber, capacity, location, status
### Note: This is a PUBLIC route - anyone can view tables


### ============================================
### 2. CREATE TABLE - Admin Only (Success)
### ============================================
### IMPORTANT: First login as admin in 01-auth.rest and copy token above
POST {{baseUrl}}/tables
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "tableNumber": 1,
  "capacity": 4,
  "location": "Window side",
  "status": "active"
}

### Expected Response: 201 Created
### Returns: Created table object with _id
### Copy the _id and update @tableId variable above


### ============================================
### 3. CREATE TABLE - Different Capacity
### ============================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/tables
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "tableNumber": 2,
  "capacity": 6,
  "location": "Patio",
  "status": "active"
}

### Expected Response: 201 Created


